29 (C) A person listed in subdivision (i)(2)(A) of this
30 section who is notified of the arrest or detention of a juvenile by the
31 superintendent or the designee of the superintendent shall maintain the
32 confidentiality of the information he or she receives.
33 (3) The arrest information shall be used by the school only for
34 the limited purpose of obtaining services for the juvenile or to ensure
35 school safety.
