As Engrossed: H3/19/25 SB320
1 heard, the court may:
2 (i) Order deoxyribonucleic acid (DNA) testing to
3 determine whether the putative parent is the biological parent of the
4 juvenile;
5 (ii) Enter an order:
6 (a) Finding that the putative parent does not
7 have rights to the juvenile;
8 (b) Dismissing the putative parent from the
9 action; and
10 (c) Finding that no further notice is due to
