1 9-27-312. Notification to defendants.
2 (a) In a delinquency and family-in-need-of-services case, a juvenile
3 defendant ten (10) years of age and above, any persons having care and
4 control of the juveniles, and all adult defendants shall be served with a
5 copy of the petition and either a notice of hearing or order to appear in the
6 manner provided by the Arkansas Rules of Civil Procedure.
7 (b) In a dependent-neglected case:
8 (1) A juvenile respondent shall be served with a copy of the
9 petition and all other pleadings by serving the juvenile's attorney ad litem
10 in accordance with Rule 5 of the Arkansas Rules of Civil Procedure; and
11 (2) Each adult defendant shall be served in the manner provided
12 in the Arkansas Rules of Civil Procedure with a copy of the petition and
13 either a notice of a hearing or an order to appear.
