24 and the juvenile has been absent from his or her home or domicile for more
25 than twenty-four (24) hours, the juvenile may be held in custody in a
26 juvenile detention facility for purposes of identification, processing, or
27 arranging for release or transfer to an alternative facility.
28 (ii) The holding shall be limited to the minimum time
29 necessary to complete these actions and shall not occur in any facility
30 utilized for incarceration of adults.
