21 attorney ad litem.
22 (3) Each attorney ad litem shall:
23 (A) File written motions, responses, or objections at all
24 stages of the proceedings when necessary to protect the best interest of the
25 juvenile;
26 (B) Attend all hearings and participate in all telephone
27 conferences with the court unless excused by the court; and
28 (C) Present witnesses and exhibits when necessary to
29 protect the juvenile's best interest.
30 (4) An attorney ad litem shall be provided access to all records
