32 records, medical records, all court records relating to the juvenile and his
33 or her family, and records, including those maintained electronically and in
34 the case management system, of the Department of Human Services relating to
35 the juvenile and his or her family to the extent permitted by federal law.
36 (5)(A) An attorney ad litem shall represent the best interest of
