19 (D) A foster parent, adoptive parent, preadoptive parent,
20 or relative caregiver may not offer evidence to be considered by the court
21 unless he or she is called as a witness.
22 (m)(1)(A) A grandparent shall be entitled to notice and shall be
23 granted an opportunity to be heard in any dependency-neglect proceeding
24 involving a grandchild who is twelve (12) months of age or younger when:
25 (i) The grandchild resides with this grandparent for
