As Engrossed: H3/19/25 SB320
1 (c) Any other factors that the court deems
2 relevant.
3 (D) When practicable and appropriate, the court may
4 utilize mandatory attendance to such programs as well as community service
5 requirements in lieu of a fine;
6 (8) Assess a court cost of no more than thirty-five dollars
7 ($35.00) to be paid by the juvenile, his or her parent, both parents, the
8 guardian, or the custodian; and
9 (9) Order a juvenile service fee not to exceed twenty dollars
10 ($20.00) per month to be paid by the juvenile, his or her parent, both
11 parents, the guardian, or the custodian.
12 (b) The court may provide that any violation of its orders shall
13 subject the parent, both parents, the juvenile, custodian, or guardian to
14 contempt sanctions.
