1 (B) In which the juvenile is enrolled; or
2 (C) From which the juvenile receives services.
3 (g) The prosecuting attorney shall notify the school superintendent or
4 the designee of the school superintendent of the school district to which the
5 juvenile transfers, in which the juvenile is enrolled, or from which the
6 juvenile receives services if the juvenile is adjudicated delinquent for:
7 (1) An offense:
8 (A) For which the juvenile could have been charged as an
