9 every effort possible to notify the custodial parent, guardian, or custodian
10 of the juvenile's location and may:
11 (A)(i) Take the juvenile to detention.
12 (ii) The intake officer shall be notified immediately
13 to make a detention decision under § 9-35-416 within twenty-four (24) hours
14 of the time the juvenile was first taken into custody, and the prosecuting
15 attorney shall be notified within twenty-four (24) hours.
16 (iii) If the juvenile remains in detention, a
17 detention hearing shall be held no later than seventy-two (72) hours after
18 the juvenile is taken into custody or if the seventy-two (72) hours ends on a
19 Saturday, Sunday, or holiday, on the next business day;
